{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_62","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'git show --stat --summary ai/vjovanov/fix-native-image-run-io.netty-netty-common-4.2.1.Final --'","aggregated_output":"commit e259a69513 (HEAD -> master, origin/master, ai/vjovanov/fix-native-image-run-io.netty-netty-common-4.2.1.Final)\nAuthor: Mihailo Markovic <96449436+kimeta@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   20 minutes ago\n\n    Improve and ground Forge workflow specifications (#7227)\n    \n    * Adopt grund v2 for Forge docs and code citations\n    \n    Migrate the Forge documentation set to grund v2: restructure docs by component (workflows/, roadmap.md, strategies.md), adopt FS/AR/WF/STRAT/ORCH/GIT/E2E/BENCH/ROADMAP kinds with inline §<ID> citations, add the strict .agents/grund.toml, and weave code citations into Forge docstrings.\n    \n    * Reconcile Forge v2 docs with merged master behavior\n    \n    After rebasing the grund v2 docs onto master, fold in behavior that landed upstream so the v2 specs match the merged implementation:\n    \n    - Rewrite the library-update request handling to match #6848: document title-coordinate target resolution (in-place vs clone/split) and the prompt-based reporter-requested-metadata contract (forward the issue body to the agent, infer needs, exercise via public API, add typeReached), replacing the earlier post-generation parse-and-merge description that #6848 removed. Add the Library update target glossary term.\n    \n    - Add the legacy test-only Native Image config rejection to local CI-equivalent verification (#5822).\n    \n    - Add the generated-test validity gate that routes known broken-behavior tests to the dynamic-access definition of done (#6254).\n    \n    * Skip inline code spans in checkDocLinks\n    \n    checkDocLinks blanked fenced code blocks before parsing links but left\n    inline code spans intact, so placeholder link syntax shown as inline\n    code (`[<path>](<path>)` in the grund declaration examples in AGENTS.md,\n    CLAUDE.md, and forge/AGENTS.md) was parsed as a broken repo-local link\n    and failed the Check documentation links job.\n    \n    Blank the contents of inline code spans (matching backtick runs) before\n    link parsing, replacing span characters with spaces so link line numbers\n    stay accurate. Mirrors the existing fenced-code-block handling.\n    \n    * Add forge/docs README explaining doc structure and grund tags\n    \n    Add an index README to forge/docs that maps the documentation set by\n    grund kind (which file or folder each prefix lives in), lists every doc\n    with its primary declaration, describes the workflows/ subtree and its\n    per-workflow split, and explains the grund tagging convention used\n    throughout: ID format, declarations, §-citations, cross-namespace\n    references, and the grund commands for resolving a citation.\n    \n    * Document new-library-support workflow and fix Forge FS citations\n    \n    - Add forge/docs/workflows/add-new-library-support.md for the\n      library-new-request workflow, citing the dynamic-access docs rather than\n      restating them, and declare WF-basic-iterative as the fallback engine.\n    - Fix the broken cross-namespace citation to the reachability repo's library\n      version update automation (now §root/FS-library-version-update-automation).\n    - Trim FS-forge-issue-resolution-goal to a minimal grund-citing intro and move\n      the fails-* queue origin into a Scope subsection.\n    - Replace the workflow catalog prose with a driver-to-spec table and drop the\n      incorrect \"(Future) Basic iterative workflow\" note.\n    \n    * Address review: fix doc path, generalize branch contract, mark divergence ticket as future work\n    \n    - native_test_verification.py: correct hanging doc reference to\n      native-metadata-tracing.md\n    - native-metadata-tracing.md: align reporter/tracer divergence spec with\n      actual behavior (log + Codex fallback); mark upstream ticket filing as\n      future work\n    - functional-spec.md: generalize the feature-branch output contract to\n      ai/<login>/<suffix> across all Forge workflows\n    \n    * Consolidate workflow-system and code-coverage docs and tag them WF\n    \n    Both the workflow-system functional-spec/architecture pair and the\n    code-coverage-improvement subfolder split each fact across two files that\n    were really one overview. Merge each into a single file, and tag every ID in\n    docs/workflows/ — including architecture — with the WF prefix so the kind\n    matches the folder home:\n    \n    - workflows/architecture.md now declares WF-forge-workflow-system,\n      WF-forge-workflow-architecture (was AR-forge-workflow-system),\n      WF-forge-workflow-engine, and WF-forge-workflow-strategy-config;\n      workflows/functional-spec.md is removed.\n    - workflows/code-coverage-improvement.md replaces the\n      code-coverage-improvement/ subfolder, declaring WF-code-coverage-improvement\n      and WF-code-coverage-improvement-architecture (was AR-code-coverage-improvement).\n    \n    All citations across AGENTS.md, docs/architecture.md, agent.md, roadmap.md,\n    strategies.md, workflow-drivers.md, and the README index are updated to the\n    new IDs.\n    \n    * Cite index-validation safeguard from PR review spec\n    \n    The rebase integrated master's #7590 final-index-validation behavior as the\n    grounded FS-index-validation-safeguard declaration; cite it from\n    FS-automated-pr-review's merge-gate clause so the new spec point is reachable.\n\n .agents/grund.toml                                 |  61 ++\n .../verify-new-library-version-compatibility.yml   |   2 +\n AGENTS.md                                          |  42 ++\n docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md                            | 119 +++-\n docs/goals.md                                      |  19 +\n docs/grund.md                                      |  18 +\n forge/.agents/grund.